SUMMARY:Seattle AI Startup Showcase in March
DESCRIPTION:üöÄ Seattle AI Startup Showcase\n‚ÄãJoin us for an energizing evening spotlighting Seattle‚Äôs rising AI founders ‚Äî and helping bold ideas find the talent\, teammates\, and momentum they need. \n‚ÄãüìÖ Main Event: AI Startup Showcase\n‚ÄãExperience high-impact pitches from 5‚Äì10 hand-picked AI startups solving real problems at the frontier. \n‚Äã‚è±Ô∏è Format: 5-minute pitch + 5-minute live Q&A with judges and audience. \n‚Äãü§ù Goal: Real problems\, real solutions\, and real teams building for the future. \n‚Äãüëâ Building something? Apply to Pitch Here\nDeadline: March 16th \n‚Äãüé§ Special Feature: ‚ÄúDay Zero‚Äù Panel\n‚ÄãWe‚Äôre kicking off the showcase with a candid conversation featuring veteran VCs and operators on what it takes to win in the 2026 AI landscape. \n‚ÄãKey Topics: \n‚Äãüí° The VC Playbook ‚Äì What investors look for before Product-Market Fit. \n‚Äãü§ñ The AI Shift ‚Äì How AI is reshaping venture dynamics and investment criteria. \n‚Äãüìñ Narrative ‚Äì How storytelling and timing influence funding outcomes. \n‚Äãüå± For Aspiring Founders\n‚ÄãNot a founder yet‚Äîbut have an idea? \n‚ÄãA select group of 8‚Äì10 aspiring builders will deliver 1-minute elevator pitches to attract co-founders and early believers. If you‚Äôre ready to start\, this is your room. \n‚Äãüåü Featured Panelists & Judges\n‚Äãüåü Brooke Borseth | Senior Associate\, FUSE\nBrooke partners with founders from Day Zero through Series A. Previously at Moneta Ventures\, she led high-impact investments and served as a Board Observer for multiple high-growth startups\, bringing a board-level lens on scaling from idea to category-defining company. \n‚ÄãüöÄ Nate Bek | Senior Associate & Head of Research\, Ascend\nNate leads investing and market intelligence at Ascend\, one of the PNW‚Äôs most active early-stage firms. A former GeekWire VC reporter\, he blends analytical rigor with narrative insight‚Äîunderstanding how ecosystem trends and market stories drive breakout outcomes. \n‚Äãüî• Hang Huang | Co-Founder & CEO\, InsForge\nHang is building the infrastructure layer for agentic development at InsForge. The company has raised $1.5M and is seeing rapid weekly growth. A former Amazon PM and Yale MBA\, he brings the founder‚Äôs real-world perspective to the conversation. \n‚ÄãAbout B.E.L.L.E\nWe are B.E.L.L.E (Boundless; Entrepreneurship; Liberty; Liaison; Empowerment)\, a community of entrepreneurs dedicated to breaking boundaries and building futures. \nOur Impact: We‚Äôve connected over 25\,000 people\, supported more than 600 startups\, and collectively they raised $1 billion in funding!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/seattle-ai-startup-showcase-in-march/
LOCATION:12021 Northup Way Suite 202\, Bellevue
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence,Developer,Startups
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/2.png
ORGANIZER;CN="B.E.L.L.E Community":MAILTO:info@belle.community
END:VEVENT
