SUMMARY:ctrl+alt+create live: Vibe Coding for Everybody
DESCRIPTION:‚Äãhttps://ctrlaltcreate.live/ \n‚ÄãAnybody Can Build Software with AI. No Experience? We‚Äôll Help You Get Started. \n‚ÄãOne Registered Participant Will Get a $100 Amazon Gift Card! \n‚ÄãPresented by Every\, this is a community-oriented\, beginner-friendly workshop series that‚Äôs fun for techies & non-technical people alike. \n‚ÄãRegister to participate either in-person (in Seattle) or online. \n‚ÄãIf you need to use AI but don‚Äôt know where to start\, this is for you. If you‚Äôve been building with AI\, then you‚Äôre also welcome! \n‚ÄãWe‚Äôll help you build something in just 2 hours. Fast\, fun\, and zero skills required. And if you know what you‚Äôre doing\, great! \n‚ÄãSeriously\, Anyone Can Build Something. \n‚ÄãWe‚Äôre bringing together non-technical users with big ideas and technical users who share a passion for AI and vibe coding. It‚Äôs a creative melting pot where curiosity meets capability. \n‚ÄãLearn how to begin: We show you how to use AI tools that respond to plain English. It‚Äôs easy to get started with vibe coding. \n‚Äã2-Hour Sprint: Fast\, high-energy\, and satisfying. You could walk away with a real project or prototype. \n‚ÄãLow Stakes\, High Reward: Experiment without fear. Plus\, a random attendee will get a $100 Amazon Gift Card! \n‚ÄãIn-Person & Virtual: We host regular workshops in tech hubs like Seattle\, while welcoming virtual participants from anywhere in the world. \n‚ÄãAll Ages Welcome: Kids and students are encouraged to participate alongside adults. \n‚ÄãWho Is This For? \n‚ÄãThe Daydreamer: Would-be entrepreneurs who have never launched their own idea. Turn ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù into a functional prototype in two hours. \n‚ÄãThe Idea Hunter: Curious entrepreneurs waiting for inspiration to strike. Test concepts quickly and find your next big venture. \n‚ÄãThe Tech-Adjacent: People who work in tech but aren‚Äôt software developers. Master the tools that allow you to build without engineering tickets. \n‚ÄãThe Upskiller: Looking for work or better positioning? Build a portfolio of AI-powered projects to prove your value in the modern workforce. \n‚ÄãThe Creative: Artists\, designers\, or writers. Learn how to bridge the gap between your imagination and a working digital product. \n‚ÄãThe Experimenter: This is your chance to try AI tools or build with low stakes. No pressure\, no wrong answers‚Äîjust create.
