DESCRIPTION:Global Security Tour ‚Äì Seattle 2026\nHosted by Seattle Data\, AI & Security \nüìÖ Saturday\, April 4\, 2026\nüïò 9:00 AM ‚Äì 6:00 PM\nüìç Bellevue City Hall\nüéüÔ∏è RSVP: Free (Limited capacity)\nüë• 500+ expected | Enterprise + Startup leaders in one room \nThe first Global Security Tour launches in Seattle ‚Äî and it starts with a Microsoft executive keynote.\nIf you‚Äôre responsible for security outcomes\, budgets\, platforms\, or strategy\, this is the room you want to be in.\n‚úÖ Keynote: Corporate Vice President (Microsoft) ‚Äì Sentinel Data Lake\n‚úÖ Microsoft product leaders attending across Security Copilot\, Microsoft Sentinel\, Defender\, and Purview\n‚úÖ Women in Tech panel featuring senior voices and real career leadership stories\n‚úÖ Hackathon experience (build / learn / collaborate ‚Äî details coming soon)\n‚úÖ High-value networking with senior enterprise leaders\, founders\, and builders \nWhy Directors & VPs are showing up \nSee where unified security operations is going ‚Äî straight from the leaders building it\nGet practical direction on how enterprises are approaching modern SecOps (without the salesy fluff)\nMeet peers facing the same challenges: scale\, visibility\, governance\, SOC efficiency\, and AI adoption\nBuild relationships that matter ‚Äî Microsoft leaders\, enterprise decision-makers\, and startups solving real problems\nWhat to expect (speaker roster + detailed agenda coming soon) \nMicrosoft executive keynote\nLeadership sessions + discussions (Sentinel / Defender / Purview / Security Copilot ecosystem)\nWomen in Tech panel\nNetworking blocks built for meaningful conversations\nPerks \nFree registration (limited seats)\nBreakfast + lunch + coffee included\nSwag\, giveaways & strong networking energy\nThis isn‚Äôt just another security event ‚Äî it‚Äôs the start of a tour and a community movement.\nIf you want early access to the conversations shaping security platforms and AI-powered SecOps\, register now. \nüëâ