SUMMARY:Crescendo: A Symphonic Celebration of Washington Landscapes
DESCRIPTION:Join Northwest Symphony Orchestra and Washington Trails Association for their third annual celebration of music and nature. Be transported to the wilderness as you experience photos from WTA‚Äôs Northwest Exposure Photo Contest on the big screen while listening to the sweeping melodies of Ravel\, Bizet\, Grieg\, Wagner and more performed live by NWSO. Special guests The Musical Mountaineers will return to perform and present the world premiere of their newest short film. The concert is open to all ages\, so gather your friends and family for a truly unforgettable evening. \nBoth longstanding Washington nonprofits\, WTA and NWSO share the goal of bringing joy and beauty into people‚Äôs lives. Your ticket purchase supports NWSO‚Äôs work to promote the vibrant spectrum of classical music\, especially contemporary Northwest composers\, and WTA‚Äôs mission to connect everyone to the outdoors and build a community that gives back to trails and public lands.
