SUMMARY:Discovery Series\, Dr. Cyrus Ghjar\, Professor\, Fred Hutch
DESCRIPTION:What if cancer didn‚Äôt strike in one dramatic moment‚Äîbut instead lingered\, quietly\, for years? Long after a tumor seems gone\, cancer cells can lie dormant. And sometimes\, they return. This is the mystery of metastatic relapse‚Äîand the frontier where Dr. Cyrus Ghajar works. \n‚ÄãAt Fred Hutch Cancer Center\, Ghajar leads research into how dormant cancer cells evade treatment and what reactivates them. His lab bridges oncology\, immunology\, and bioengineering to explore the role of the immune system in suppressing dormant cancer cells. It‚Äôs a delicate numbers game that can tip the balance between remission and recurrence. \n‚ÄãSupported by the National Institutes of Health\, the Kuni Foundation\, U.S. Department of Defense and other funders\, Ghajar holds the Peter S. Lefkarites Memorial Endowed Chair. Ghajar‚Äôs work is reshaping how we think about metastasis‚Äînot as a sudden invasion\, but a slow\, stealthy process that might be intercepted. Join us to explore how silence in the body might hold the key to preventing relapse.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/discovery-series-dr-cyrus-ghjar-professor-fred-hutch/
LOCATION:Perkins Coie\, 1201 Third Avenue\, Seattle\, WA\, 98101\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/discoveryseries_drcyrusghjar.jpg
GEO:47.6070578;-122.3360757
